{
  "text": "Other outcomes. Systematic reviews have investigated the association between sedentary behavior and other health outcomes, such as bone health, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] psychosocial and motor dysfunction, [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] poor academic performance and cognitive development, [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] physical fitness, [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] and symptomatic gallstone disease. [CITATION_9] .",
